Definition.WordDefinition: Phallic \Phal"lic\, a. [Gr. ?.] Of or pertaining to the phallus, or to phallism. [1913 Webster]

phallic adj 1: relating to a phallus especially as an embodiment of generative power; "a phallic cult"; "phallic worship" 2: resembling or being a phallus; "a phallic symbol"; "phallic eroticism"; "priapic figurines" [syn: {priapic}]
